
                                            The bank encountered minor glitches with its banking app on Saturday follow another outage on Friday which left customers frustrated.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - FNB says its technicians will continue to monitor its systems after experiencing technical problems. The bank encountered minor glitches with its banking app on Saturday follow another outage on Friday which left customers frustrated. People were unable to withdraw cash and access other services. The bank, however, says all its systems are now operating fully. Spokesperson Peter Alkema said: “We continue to be very grateful for our customers’ understanding when we have glitches and as promised we’re back online.”